    },
    {
      "day": 2,
      "type": "value",
      "subject": "7 Things Every Builder Must Know",
      "preview": "Avoid these common mistakes and take control of your builds",
      "body": "Hey there,\n\nIn my last email, I gave you a high-level overview of the OLYMPUS Builder Dashboard and how it can transform your build process. Today, I want to dive a little deeper and share 7 key things every builder needs to know.\n\n1. You can't fix what you can't see. Most teams struggle with lack of visibility, making it nearly impossible to identify and address issues early on.\n\n2. Status meetings are a waste of time. The dashboard gives you real-time updates, so you can skip the meetings and focus on building.\n\n3. Agents don't always know best. The dashboard shows you the reasoning behind key decisions, so you can understand (and even challenge) the logic.\n\n4. Compliance is critical. The dashboard tracks constitutional checks to ensure your builds meet the necessary standards.\n\n5. Risks are inevitable. But the dashboard helps you identify and mitigate them before they derail your project.\n\n6. Context is king. The dashboard provides deep insights into what was built and why, so you can make more informed decisions.\n\n7. Transparency builds trust. When your team has visibility, they're more engaged and invested in the process.\n\nThese are just a few of the game-changing benefits the OLYMPUS Dashboard can deliver. Ready to see it in action? Click the button below to get started for free.\n\nTalk soon,\n[Your Name]\nOLYMPUS Conversion Copywriter",
